Is it really about getting coffee or are we just trying to recreate that childhood feeling, when you’d come home from school, change out of your uniform, ring your friend’s doorbell, and spend hours in the park doing absolutely nothing, yet feeling everything?

These days, just sitting next to someone without a reason feels rare. Most places outside home come with a price tag anyway, so maybe we’re just wrapping up our need for connection in a coffee cup.
